{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:18.480Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Project Listings**\n\nI'm currently refining the project listing logic. I've realized I need to handle client-specific project scoping, considering both admin/GFF admin roles and client users. The code now ensures that client users only see their projects, even if a `client_id` is accidentally requested, and that other roles can still filter.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:19.811Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Project Create Route**\n\nI've decided to incorporate a project creation route to enhance completeness and support testing. I've also confirmed that the project listing functionality is now implemented. I'm focusing on the implementation details for creating projects. The logic for filtering and providing projects is well thought out, it is now time to write the code.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:21.244Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Ticket Creation**\n\nI'm now implementing the support ticket creation route, ensuring that client users can only create tickets for their own client accounts. I've integrated checks to manage user roles and client ID validation. Admins and GFF admins have access to create tickets, while client users are restricted to their own client accounts. I've integrated this logic to provide error messages in cases where the user's information is incomplete.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:22.780Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Developing Dashboard Endpoint**\n\nI'm now creating the client dashboard endpoint. I have a plan for how to scope it based on the user's client account, except for admins. I'm building it in `backend/app/api/routes/dashboard.py` and aiming for a responsive experience. I've designed logic that dynamically filters and provides information that varies based on a user's role. I've also implemented the support ticket creation and list functions.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:23.954Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Finalizing Dashboard Endpoint**\n\nI've just added the `get_client_dashboard` function within the `/dashboard/client` endpoint. It retrieves the dashboard summary, implementing data scoping checks. I've incorporated logic to restrict access based on user role and client ID, raising HTTP exceptions for unauthorized access. The function handles user role checks effectively, ensuring that clients can only view their own dashboards, and admins have unfettered access.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:25.238Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding User Details Route**\n\nI'm now integrating a route to retrieve user details via `/api/v1/auth/me`. I plan to modify `backend/app/api/routes/auth.py` and `backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py`. I'll implement file creation and updates with an editor, adding the `@router.get(\"/me\")` decorator for fetching current user information.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:46:27.081Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Integrating New Routes**\n\nI'm now integrating new routers. I've added a few routers to the main API: `projects_router`, `support_tickets_router`, and `dashboard_router`. I'm using the `api_router` from `fastapi` and using include_router to include them. I'm assigning prefixes and tags, matching the intended URL endpoints. My current plan involves testing with pytest and `/me`, `/projects`, `/support-tickets`, and `/dashboard` endpoints.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
